<%- include('partials/header', { activePage: 'about', title: 'Our Story | Yadhee Luxury Heritage' }) %>

    <!-- Page Title Editorial Header -->
    <section class="page-title-banner" style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(30, 2, 6, 0.82), rgba(30, 2, 6, 0.65)), url('assets/hero_saree.png');">
        <div class="banner-content text-center">
            <span class="section-accent">A Generation of Preservations</span>
            <h1 class="page-main-title">The Chronicle of Yadhee</h1>
            <p class="banner-subtitle">Weaving ancient mythology, authentic pure gold, and the legacy of Indian court craftsmanship into slow-luxury heirlooms.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Detailed Prose Layout (Story Chapter 1) -->
    <section class="about-story-section">
        <div class="section-container">
            <div class="editorial-row">
                <div class="editorial-col-text reveal-on-scroll">
                    <span class="chapter-label">CHAPTER I</span>
                    <h2 class="editorial-sub-title">The Art of the Generational Hand-Loom</h2>
                    <p class="editorial-body">Every saree sculpted at Yadhee represents up to three months of intricate looming. Our master weavers work in the historical centers of Kanchipuram and Varanasi, preserving ancient techniques dating back to Chola and Mughal courts. We refuse synthetic threads, using exclusively pure mulberry silk and authentic metallic gold threads.</p>
                    <p class="editorial-body">Our patterns are not computer generated; they are drafted by generational designers reciting Sanskrit literature, weaving detailed depictions of temple chariots, peacocks (Mayuras), sacred scripts, and geometric grids (Vana Singaram) directly into the silk body. This results in a garment that is not just worn, but inherited.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="editorial-col-visual reveal-on-scroll">
                    <div class="about-image-frame">
                        <img src="assets/saree_green.png" alt="Generational silk weaving details green">
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Detailed Prose Layout (Story Chapter 2) -->
    <section class="about-story-section alt-bg">
        <div class="section-container">
            <div class="editorial-row reverse">
                <div class="editorial-col-visual reveal-on-scroll">
                    <div class="about-image-frame">
                        <img src="assets/hero_jewel.png" alt="Heirloom gold choker carving details">
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="editorial-col-text reveal-on-scroll">
                    <span class="chapter-label">CHAPTER II</span>
                    <h2 class="editorial-sub-title">Sacred Gold and Uncut Polki Diamonds</h2>
                    <p class="editorial-body">Our jewelry collections are designed to reflect the grandeur of ancient South Indian temples and royal Rajput courts. Generational goldsmiths utilize the painstaking repoussé method, hammering complex floral and mythical details out of solid 22k gold plates with steel punches, then filling the negative cavities with sacred lac.</p>
                    <p class="editorial-body">We source raw, flat-cut diamonds (Polki) and natural untreated gemstones, refusing glass fillings. Every choker, jhumka, and filigree bangle carries a registered BIS Hallmark seal alongside unique gem registry certification, cementing sovereign value that stands unchanged over centuries.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Brand Philosophy and Sourcing Seals -->
    <section class="philosophy-section">
        <div class="section-container text-center">
            <span class="section-accent">A Sacred Contract</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">The Philosophy of Slow Luxury</h2>
            <div class="philosophy-grid">
                <div class="phil-card reveal-on-scroll">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-seedling"></i>
                    <h3>Ethical Livelihoods</h3>
                    <p>By returning 65% of profits directly to our generational weavers and smiths, we protect historical craft traditions and support rural artisan families.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="phil-card reveal-on-scroll">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-ribbon"></i>
                    <h3>Verified Silk Quality</h3>
                    <p>Every hand-woven saree undergoes independent testing by the Silk Board, carrying a unique holographic Silk Mark label confirming pure Mulberry silk.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="phil-card reveal-on-scroll">
                    <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i>
                    <h3>Assayed Gold Standards</h3>
                    <p>Every piece of jewelry is stamped with the BIS Hallmark and accompanied by carat certification reports detailing diamond, ruby, and gold weight.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Testimonial Slider / Patron Chronicles -->
    <section class="patron-chronicles">
        <div class="section-container">
            <div class="section-header text-center reveal-on-scroll">
                <span class="section-accent">Patron Chronicles</span>
                <h2 class="section-title">Words From The Vault</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="testimonial-box text-center reveal-on-scroll">
                <i class="fa-solid fa-quote-left gold-text quote-icon"></i>
                <p class="patron-quote">"Yadhee has redefined how we view luxury. Draping the Crimson Rajkumari felt like wearing living art. The sheer craftsmanship and details of the gold borders are simply breathtaking. It is the pride of my bridal collection."</p>
                <span class="patron-author">Maharani Aishwarya R., London</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
